TITLE: Kevin Spacey denies new allegations of inappropriate behavior
SUMMARY: Kevin Spacey, the Oscar-winning actor, has denied new allegations of inappropriate behavior from men who will feature in a documentary on British television that is due to be released next week

TITLE: Late-season storm expected to bring heavy snowfall to the Sierra Nevada
SUMMARY: A late-season storm is expected to hit the Sierra Nevada this weekend, bringing rain and mountain snow to Northern and Central California

TITLE: Biden gives Presidential Medal of Freedom to Nancy Pelosi, Michelle Yeoh and more
SUMMARY: President Biden honored 19 people with the Presidential Medal of Freedom, including Nancy Pelosi, Al Gore, Michelle Yeoh, Katie Ledecky and more.

TITLE: Mexican officials say 3 bodies recovered in Baja California during search for missing
SUMMARY: Mexican authorities say three bodies have been recovered in an area of Baja California near where two Australians and an American went missing last weekend

SUMMARY: South Dakota Gov. Kristi Noem claims in a new book to have met with North Korean leader Kim Jong Un during her time in Congress

TITLE: Columbia student protest organizer describes a police raid on campus
SUMMARY: Columbia students were suspended after their arrests at the “Gaza Solidarity Encampment,” a tactic colleges across the country have also employed.

TITLE: Rep. Henry Cuellar, wife indicted on charges of bribes tied to Azerbaijan
SUMMARY: Texas Democratic Rep. Henry Cuellar is claiming innocence ahead of a potential indictment against him, according to a statement released from his office.

TITLE: Zebra remains on the loose as officials close trailheads to keep people away
SUMMARY: A zebra that escaped from a trailer east of Seattle last weekend remained on the lam Friday, as authorities closed off trailheads at a nature area in hopes of keeping people away and easing her capture

TITLE: Aetna agrees to settle lawsuit over fertility coverage for LGBTQ+ customers
SUMMARY: The health insurer Aetna has agreed to settle a lawsuit over whether its fertility treatment coverage discriminates against LGBTQ+ patients

TITLE: April jobs report misses expectations, signaling a possible slowdown
SUMMARY: U.S. employers added 175,000 jobs in April.

TITLE: Former UK PM Boris Johnson turned away from polling station after forgetting ID
SUMMARY: Former British Prime Minister Boris Johnson was turned away from a polling station after forgetting to bring ID to vote in the U.K.’s local elections

TITLE: Distressed sawfish rescued in Florida Keys dies after aquarium treatment
SUMMARY: An endangered sawfish rescued last month in the Florida Keys after it was spotted acting erratically and swimming in circles has died as wildlife officials continue to search for what is causing fish to become distressed

SUMMARY: More than six months after Hamas terrorists invaded Israel on Oct. 7, the Israeli military continues its bombardment of the neighboring Gaza Strip.

TITLE: LIVE:  ABC News Live
SUMMARY: 24/7 coverage of breaking news and live events

TITLE: Flood watch in effect for over 11 million people in Texas and Oklahoma
SUMMARY: A flood watch remains in effect for more than 11 million people in Texas and Oklahoma on Saturday morning as a number of flood warnings are in effect.

TITLE: WATCH:  Tornado spotted in central Texas
SUMMARY: Dramatic video shows a large tornado touching down near homes in central Texas. Gov. Greg Abbott issued a disaster declaration for dozens of counties as the state was pummeled by severe storms.

SUMMARY: Two little bears and one big mama bear were spotted outside a home in Big Bear Lake, California.

TITLE: WATCH:  Confused dog tries to play fetch with statue
SUMMARY: PJ the spaniel loves to play fetch with everyone.

SUMMARY: Keepers at the Houston Zoo knew giraffe Kamili was pregnant, but didn't know the exact delivery date — until they arrived at work one morning to find a newborn baby giraffe, named Tino.

SUMMARY: Pictures spoke louder than words as raging floodwaters swept away a bridge behind a Brazilian mayor as she delivered a storm warning.

SUMMARY: Bella has a very rare condition known as dimelia.

SUMMARY: At least five people were killed as a landmark building dubbed the “Harry Potter Castle” was damaged in a Russian attack on Monday, officials said.

TITLE: WATCH:  Mammatus clouds fill the sky as severe weather hits Kansas
SUMMARY: The distinctive clouds are formed due to sinking cold air in unstable cumulonimbus clouds.
